            <p class="section-title active center" href="#">BIO</p>
                <div class="row center hidden">
                    <div class="col-7">
                        <div class="row" style="padding:5px; text-align: justify;">
                        <!-- <div class="col-2" style="padding:50px;"> -->
                        <!--     <img src="./images/img_cv_dark.png" width="100%"/> -->
                        <!-- </div> -->
                            <p>
                            I received my BS (2016) from the Barcelona School of Industrial Engineering, and developed my BS thesis in the Institute of Robotics and industrial Informatics with Prof. Federico Thomas as main advisor.
                            I obtained my MS (2019) and PhD (2024) in Control and Automation from the University of Aalborg under the supervision of Prof. Rafal Wisniewski.
                            In 2022, I was a visiting scholar at the Mechanical and Aerospace Department of the State University of New York at Buffalo, where I worked closely with Prof. John Crassidis.
                            <!-- I am a control engineer with a deep passion towards physics and engineering, and a strong interest in understanding systems behavior through rigorous mathematics. -->
                            <!-- I am dedicated to the development of algorithms and technology for the sustainable progress of the space industry, and I value collaborative learning, recognizing it as the most effective means of acquiring knowledge and fostering innovation. -->
                            <!-- A. R. Gomez has contributed to large projects such as ESA's funded project SURE and the development of<a href="https://www.sternula.com/projects/mariot/">MARIOT</a> and SURE, -->
                            After my PhD program, I became a Postdoctoral researcher (2024) with Prof. Jakob Stoustrup as my advisor to develop an ESA funded project with the aim of enhancing safety and capabilities of launcher vehicles.
                            In addition, I have published various articles in relevant peer reviewed conferences and journals, and lectured linear algebra and differential equations to large groups of Industrial engineering students.
                            My research interest lies in safe and robust control, adaptive estimation, optimization and modelling.
                            </p>
